This paper is about dialogue systems, which are typically studied in the natural language processing (NLP) community. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a model for frame tracking, which involves memory and reasoning, suggesting that it belongs to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates its model on a dataset, indicating that it may fall under the sub-category of software development (cs.SD). Finally, the paper discusses the usability of the model for users, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
